element.name: The Phoenix by The Champions, Traditional Cache (1.5/1)
element.description: In the shadow of the Cross, the place where thousands once stood to greet the man from the "City of the seven hills" Within sight of the "White House from the Land of the Free"
element.long-description:
All items are individually packaged in zip-lock bags. As usual, take whatever tickles your fancy, and remember, you don’t have to replace an item of equal value, but if you can by all means do so.
Located in an open area with no cover, it had to be put below ground level, but it should stick out to those who seek it. *** Be careful when adding a log as it is easy to give too much away (making it too easy for future seekers to find the cache). I have had to encrypt a couple of logs from finders because of this. ***
Enjoy,
The Champions.
element.encoded-hints: Hidden underground, but clearly marked with a cement slab. The Cross in question is the Papal Cross where Pope John Paul came and held a mass there around 1980 and one can also see the American Ambassadors residence,"The White House," not too far away!

2007-08-19T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Found with Cam and Toadster. I've never actually been to this park before today and the size of it is truely impressive. A great cache - personally the largest I've seen, perhaps size has more to do with it after all. [;)]
Out - German book (not sure what it's about but my flatmate is German) and an envelope with some German clippings and what looks like a train ticket... In - cute rolly stamp and a magnetic frog
